        "city_summary": "Greenville ( GREEN-vil; locally  GREEN-vəl) is a city in Greenville County, South Carolina, United States, and its county seat. It is the sixth-most populous city in South Carolina with a population of 70,720 at the 2020 census, while the Greenville metropolitan area has an estimated 997,000 residents and is the largest metropolitan area in the state.\nGreenville is located approximately halfway between Atlanta and Charlotte along I-85; its metro area also includes I-185 and I-385.",
